Step 1: Compute Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 2,545,589.48 and Total Revenue = 5,565,589.48.
• Calculation: 2,545,589.48 / 5,565,589.48 = 0.4576 (approximately).
• Converting to percentage: 0.4576 × 100% = 45.76%

Step 2: Compute Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• This ratio is calculated as: Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities.
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable = 450,000.00 + 278,279.50 = 728,279.50.
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -81,548.37.
• Calculation: -81,548.37 / 728,279.50 ≈ -0.112 or approximately -0.11

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.76%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.11"
  }
}
